Base.Explanation: Get the Terminal Services settings for a existing user account. The settings can be obtained for Windows 2003 (and higher), Windows 2000, and Windows NT4 user accounts.

ArrayElement.Name: User Object
ArrayElement.Description: Note: Use only with Windows 2003 or higher! A data structure representing the user account. The property is used to identifiy the user account and is normally generated as a variable by a previous script action.

ArrayElement.Name: User account
ArrayElement.Description: The user account specified by the domain SAM account name. Example: Domain_A\jsmith or \\DC_A\jsmith. This property must be used with Windows 2000 and Windows NT4 networks.

ArrayElement.Name: Profile path
ArrayElement.Description: Roaming or mandatory profile path to use when the user logs on to the Terminal Server.

ArrayElement.Name: Home directory
ArrayElement.Description: Home directory for the user. Each user on a Terminal Server has a unique home directory. This ensures that application information is stored separately for each user in a multi-user environment.

ArrayElement.Name: Home directory drive
ArrayElement.Description: Home drive for the user. In a network environment, this property is a string containing a drive specification (a drive letter followed by a colon) to which the home directory is mapped.

ArrayElement.Name: Allow logon
ArrayElement.Description: Value that specifies whether the user is allowed to log on to the Terminal Server. The value is 'Yes' if logon is allowed, and 'No' if logon is not allowed.

ArrayElement.Name: Enable remote control
ArrayElement.Description: Value that specifies whether to allow remote observation or remote control of the user's Terminal Services session. For a description of these values, see the online help.

ArrayElement.Name: Max. disconnection time
ArrayElement.Description: Maximum amount of time, in minutes, that a disconnected Terminal Services session remains active on the Terminal Server. After the specified number of minutes have elapsed, the session is terminated.

ArrayElement.Name: Max. connection time
ArrayElement.Description: Maximum duration, in minutes, of the Terminal Services session. After the specified number of minutes have elapsed, the session can be disconnected or terminated.

ArrayElement.Name: Max. idle time
ArrayElement.Description: Maximum amount of time, in minutes, that the Terminal Services session can remain idle. After the specified number of minutes have elapsed, the session can be disconnected or terminated.

ArrayElement.Name: Reconnection action
ArrayElement.Description: Value that specifies whether to allow reconnection to a disconnected Terminal Services session from any client computer. The value is 'TRUE' if reconnection is allowed from the original client computer only, and 'FALSE' if reconnection from any client computer is allowed. Note: This property applies only to Citrix ICA clients.

ArrayElement.Name: Broken connection action
ArrayElement.Description: Value that specifies the action to take when a Terminal Services session limit is reached. The value is 'TRUE' if the client session should be terminated, and 'FALSE' if the client session should be disconnected.

ArrayElement.Name: Client drives at logon
ArrayElement.Description: Value that specifies whether to reconnect to mapped client drives at logon. The value is 'TRUE' if reconnection is enabled, and 'FALSE' if reconnection is disabled. Note: This property applies only to Citrix ICA clients.

ArrayElement.Name: Client printers at logon
ArrayElement.Description: Value that specifies whether to reconnect to mapped client printers at logon. The value is 'TRUE' if reconnection is enabled, and 'FALSE' if reconnection is disabled.

ArrayElement.Name: Default printer
ArrayElement.Description: Value that specifies whether to print automatically to the client's default printer. The value is 'TRUE' if printing to the client's default printer is enabled, and 'FALSE' if it is disabled.

ArrayElement.Name: Working directory
ArrayElement.Description: Working directory path for the user.

ArrayElement.Name: Initial program
ArrayElement.Description: Path and filename of the application that the user wants to start automatically when the user logs on to the Terminal Server.

TableDefinition.DatabaseQuery: SELECT u.ID, u.[Profile Name], u.[Enrollment Time], u.[Reset Time], u.[Block Time], u.[Reset Count], u.[Block Count], u.Blocked FROM [Enrolled Users] u WHERE CONVERT(varchar(500),u.[Account Name]) = '%AD_canonicalName_sql%'
SELECT a.[Account ID], a.Question FROM [Enrolled Users] u INNER JOIN [User Answers] a ON u.ID = a.[Account ID] WHERE CONVERT(varchar(500),u.[Account Name]) = '%AD_canonicalName_sql%'
